<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,373,1265]" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1021,1047]" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Distribution</emphasis>
:—Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[507,575,1022,1048]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in the Atlantic Forest Biome, occurring from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1224,1374,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[312,503,1058,1084]" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" refId="ref24997" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (2012) Tibouchina. In: Baumgratz, J. F. A., Bernardo, K. F. R., Chiavegatto, B., Goldenberg, R., Guimaraes, P. J. F., Kriebel, R., Martins, A. B., Michelangeli, F. A., Reginato, M., Romero, R., Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Woodgyer, E. (Eds.) Melastomataceae: Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed July 2012)." type="url" year="2012">Guimarães 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,373,1265]" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1093,1119]" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, it is restricted to Shrubby 
<emphasis box="[823,921,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Restinga</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[977,1075,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Restinga</emphasis>
Forest. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[1168,1425,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichopoda">
<emphasis box="[1168,1425,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="86">Tibouchina trichopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by leaves with 3–5 basal acrodromous veins, marginal veins not diverging from the inner ones, appressedstrigulose adaxial surface, and abaxial surface with sericeous blade and appressed-hirtellous acrodromous venation. In addition, involucral and concave bracteoles, and the filaments basally glandular-pubescent also identify this species. Additional illustrations in 
